This recommended practice is intended to be a basic or primary document that can be utilized and referenced by owners of electric motors that need repair as well as by owners and operators of establishments that offer motor repair services. It has been developed primarily for the needs of the petroleum and chemical industry but can be adapted to other applications. The use of this recommended practice by users and repair facilities is expected to result in higher-quality, more cost-effective, and timely repairs. It also provides a means of evaluating repairs and facilities.<<ETX>>